    {"repo": "github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0", "path": "examples/create-update-delete-deployment/main.go", "symbol": "main"}
  ],
  "text": "The canonical patterns for deploying new services span three key locations across two repositories:\n\n1. **API Type Definition** (`github.com/sg-evals/api--v0.32.0`, `apps/v1/types.go`): The authoritative `Deployment` struct is defined in the `apps/v1` package. This is the stable, non-deprecated version (introduced in Kubernetes 1.9), as opposed to the deprecated `apps/v1beta1/types.go`, `apps/v1beta2/types.go`, and `extensions/v1beta1/types.go` variants. The struct embeds `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`, and contains a `DeploymentSpec` (with fields for `Replicas`, `Selector`, `Template`, `Strategy`, `MinReadySeconds`, `RevisionHistoryLimit`, `Paused`, and `ProgressDeadlineSeconds`) and a `DeploymentStatus`.\n\n2. **Client-side Code Pattern** (`github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0`, `examples/create-update-delete-deployment/main.go`): The canonical Go example demonstrates how to create a Deployment using the typed client. It uses `clientset.AppsV1().Deployments(namespace)` to get a deployments client, constructs an `appsv1.Deployment` struct, and calls `deploymentsClient.Create(ctx, deployment, metav1.CreateOptions{})`. It also shows Update (with retry-on-conflict pattern), List, and Delete operations.\n\n3. **Developer Documentation** (`github.com/sg-evals/client-go--v0.32.0`, `examples/create-update-delete-deployment/README.md`): The README in the `create-update-delete-deployment` example directory explains the full deployment workflow — how to build and run the example, what each step does (Create, Update, List, Delete), expected output, cleanup instructions, and troubleshooting tips. The top-level `examples/README.md` also serves as an index pointing to this example as the canonical 'Managing resources with API' reference."
}

